The paper discusses a model for question answering that incorporates task-specific embeddings, specifically for the use case of causality. This suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves training embeddings using specific contexts, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS).
